sub_title: Product Service System Design & User Research
summary:
A Product Service System Designer and User Resesearcher working at the cross section of Human Centered Design and Behavioural Psychology. With a background in Visual communication Design and  9 years of experience as a multidisciplinary Designer my design process is focused on problem solving using a systems thinking approach, driving solutions to wicked problems through user needs.

I create design solutions where a human centered approach to problem solving is applied in designing integrated product- service systems. I have keen interest in behavioural design, human psychology and a strong belief that all design decisions should be driven by sound user research, aimed at either solving a problem or fulfilling a user need. Given my eternal love for solving puzzles, mapping user journeys and joining the dots is what keeps my heart kicking!
